## DESCRIPTION

Install the gems specified in your gems.rb(5). If this is the first
time you run bundle install (and a `gems.locked` does not exist),
Bundler will fetch all remote sources, resolve dependencies and
install all needed gems.

If a `gems.locked` does exist, and you have not updated your gems.rb(5),
Bundler will fetch all remote sources, but use the dependencies
specified in the `gems.locked` instead of resolving dependencies.

If a `gems.locked` does exist, and you have updated your gems.rb(5),
Bundler will use the dependencies in the `gems.locked` for all gems
that you did not update, but will re-resolve the dependencies of
gems that you did update. You can find more information about this
update process below under [CONSERVATIVE UPDATING][].

## OPTIONS

To apply any of these options every time `bundle install` is run,
use `bundle config` (see bundle-config(1)).

* `--clean`:
  On finishing the installation Bundler is going to remove any gems not present
  in the current gems.rb(5). Don't worry, gems currently in use will not be
  removed.

* `--full-index`:
  Bundler will not call Rubygems' API endpoint (default) but download and cache
  a (currently big) index file of all gems. Performance can be improved for
  large bundles that seldomly change by enabling this option.

* `--gemfile=<gemfile>`:
  The location of the gems.rb(5) which Bundler should use. This defaults
  to a gems.rb(5) in the current working directory. In general, Bundler
  will assume that the location of gems.rb(5) is also the project's
  root and will try to find `gems.locked` and `vendor/cache` relative
  to this location.

* `--jobs=[<number>]`:
  The maximum number of parallel download and install jobs. The default
  is `1`.

* `--local`:
  Do not attempt to connect to `rubygems.org`. Instead, Bundler will use the
  gems already present in Rubygems' cache or in `vendor/cache`. Note that if a
  appropriate platform-specific gem exists on `rubygems.org` it will not be
  found.

* `--deployment`:
  In [deployment mode][DEPLOYMENT MODE], Bundler will 'roll-out' the bundle for
  production or CI use. Please check carefully if you want to have this option
  enabled in your development environment.

* `--force`:
  Force download every gem, even if the required versions are already available
  locally.

