## DEPLOYMENT MODE

Bundler's defaults are optimized for development. To switch to
defaults optimized for deployment, use the `--deployment` flag.
Do not activate deployment mode on development machines, as it
will cause an error when the gems.rb(5) is modified.

1. A `gems.locked` is required.

   To ensure that the same versions of the gems you developed with
   and tested with are also used in deployments, a `gems.locked`
   is required.

   This is mainly to ensure that you remember to check your
   `gems.locked` into version control.

2. The `gems.locked` must be up to date

   In development, you can modify your gems.rb(5) and re-run
   `bundle install` to [conservatively update][CONSERVATIVE UPDATING]
   your `gems.locked` snapshot.

   In deployment, your `gems.locked` should be up-to-date with
   changes made in your gems.rb(5).

3. Gems are installed to `vendor/bundle`

